[ a                      owl:Axiom ;
  rdfs:comment           "Supporting evidence statement (PMID:24004951): For co-IP assays we expressed all the factors in HEK293T cells. As a control, the ligand DBL-1 interacts with the type I receptor SMA-6 but not the type II receptor DAF-4\n(Fig. 5E), consistent with previous findings that BMP2 and BMP4, the closest homologs of DBL-1, have a higher affinity to type I receptors than to type II receptors (Allendorph et al., 2006)." ;
  lego:evidence          :6168d1e000001108 ;
  dc:contributor         "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1706-4196" ;
  dc:date                "2021-10-25" ;
  pav:providedBy         "http://www.wormbase.org" ;
